data.description: This immaculate Maeser home welcomes guests with stunning landscaping complete with waterfall, stream and a variety of trees and perennials. Its large, covered porch, formal living room, and open great room wired for surround sound are perfect for entertaining. The LVP flooring, rustic floating shelves, upgraded carpeting and custom cabinetry with quartz, butcherblock and granite countertops in the kitchen, great room and bathrooms are sure to impress. The luxurious stainless-steel appliances including a double electric oven and double electric water heaters cost next to nothing to operate with the owned SOLAR panels. You can even charge an EV on the Solar power with extra power left over. The oversized 3-car garage and RV parking area give you plenty of room for all your toys. The master bedroom, ensuite, and laundry room are all on the 1st floor along with a 2nd bedroom making main-floor living a reality. The spacious 2nd floor has 4 bedrooms, a large bathroom with a private toilet and shower and a large loft area to use as an additional family room, playroom, or theater. The expansive yard is fully fenced and private with a patio and large garden area and includes the convenience of a double-wide gate from the side street for easy access to the back yard. There is plenty of room on the 1/3 acre to build a shop or put in a sports court if you wish. There is even room to grow in the spacious unfinished basement with loads of room for all the storage you need including a large cold storage room under the front porch. You will have comfort in knowing the furnace was replaced in 2021 so it has lots of life left on it. This home is in a sought-after neighborhood with custom homes, close to ATV trails and separate from the busyness of the city but at the same time close to the best Vernal shopping and quick access to Hwy 40. Square footage figures are provided as a courtesy only. Buyer is advised to obtain an independent measurement.
